<HEADLINE>
<P>
PENINSULA SCHOOLS ANNEXATION OF EASTVIEW BACKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rancho Palos Verdes City Council has approved a resolution supporting the 
annexation by the Palos Verdes Peninsula Unified School District of the 
Eastview area of the city, which is now served by the Los Angeles Unified 
School District. 
</P>
<P>
About 8,500 residents live in the Eastview area, which was annexed to Rancho 
Palos Verdes in 1983. While youngsters living in Eastview attend Los Angeles 
district schools, the rest of Rancho Palos Verdes is served by the Palos Verdes 
school district. Residents have said they are not dissatisfied with the quality 
of education in the Los Angeles district but want to complete the annexation 
process. 
</P>
<P>
"What we need is your support," Craig Kelford, an Eastview resident and 
co-chairman of Residents for Unified Local Education (RULE), told council 
members Tuesday before they voted for the resolution. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles school district has opposed the transfer, saying it would harm 
integration efforts in the San Pedro-Lomita area by removing a significant 
number of Anglo children from the schools. 
</P>
<P>
RULE is putting together a task force of public agencies and Eastview residents 
to work on the annexation proposal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
