<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BSD Bancorp's wholly owned trust subsidiary, North American Trust Co., has 
taken over management of the "vast majority" of 400 employee benefit accounts 
representing $21 million in assets that formerly were administered by 
Sacramento-based First Independent Trust Co. 
</P>
<P>
First Independent Trust had been placed in receivership by the State Department 
of Banking in May. 
</P>
<P>
North American Trust has more than 7,500 accounts with more than $800 million 
in assets under administration. The subsidiary previously was owned by BSD's 
Bank of San Diego subsidiary. The business was transferred to the holding 
company on March 31, 1988. 
</P>
