<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CERRITOS; 
</P>
<P>
DIAL-A-RIDE SERVICE WILL BEGIN OPERATION SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Starting Saturday, senior citizens and handicapped residents of Cerritos can 
call a new dial-a-ride service when they want to travel around the community, 
be it to a shopping mall, a doctor's office or a friend's house for lunch. 
</P>
<P>
The curb-to-curb service, recently approved by the City Council, is being 
provided under a contract with the Orange County Transit District, which will 
provide a wheelchair-accessible van every day of the week except Sunday and 
major holidays. 
</P>
<P>
Service will be offered from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through Friday and from 10 
a.m. to 4 p.m. Saturdays. A one-way ride will cost 80 cents. 
</P>
<P>
The service area includes parts of Norwalk, La Palma, Lakewood and Bellflower. 
It extends north to Alondra Boulevard, east to Valley View Avenue, south to Del 
Amo Boulevard and west to Bellflower Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Riders must make reservations on the same day as the trip by calling 402-RIDE 
or (714) 761-1910. 
</P>
</TEXT>
