SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: POMONA; 
</P>
<P>
CAMPUS LIBRARY DEDICATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An expansion of the Cal Poly Pomona Library was dedicated in a ceremony that 
also marked the addition of the repository's 500,000th volume. 
</P>
<P>
University President Hugh La Bounty and library Director Harold Schleifer on 
Monday officially opened the $7.4-million expansion, which added two new floors 
to the three-story library. The expansion can seat 2,600. 
</P>
<P>
"When the university opened in 1938, the library was one room, measuring 33 
feet by 45 feet, so we've come a long way," said Norm Schneider, a university 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Poly Pomona, part of the California State University system, has 19,000 
students. 
</P>
