<P>
CLEANUP OF BEACHES PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Coastal Commission will hold its annual "Adopt-A-Beach" cleanup 
program at beaches throughout the state Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The program, which asks volunteers to help remove debris from the state's sandy 
waterfront, will start at Malibu's Surfrider Beach beginning at 9 a.m. and will 
include similar stops at beaches in Santa Monica, Playa del Rey and Venice. 
Last year, the program attracted nearly 6,000 volunteers throughout California 
who removed almost 200,000 pounds of debris, according to coastal officials. 
</P>
<P>
For more information about the Malibu Beach cleanup, call (213) 456-4143. Those 
wishing to work in Venice should call (213) 396-8321 or 578-6242. For 
information about the Santa Monica cleanup effort, call (213) 374-7473. 
