<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: POMONA; 
</P>
<P>
DEVELOPMENT PANEL'S FUTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pomona City Council has delayed until Oct. 9 a decision on whether to use 
$198,000 in redevelopment funds to restore a city subsidy to the Pomona 
Economic Development Corp., which promotes the city's economic growth. 
</P>
<P>
The development panel had been financed by a 30% surcharge on business license 
fees until the council decided in June to terminate its subsidy, effective 
Sept. 15, and use the revenue instead to hire more police officers. 
</P>
<P>
The new budget proposed by the agency outlines specific tasks that it would do 
for the city, such as gathering demographic information and persuading 
businesses to establish new facilities in Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman C. L. (Clay) Bryant said the agency is providing worthwhile 
services, but Councilwoman Nell Soto said the agency needs to broaden its goals 
and revamp its board to better represent the community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
