<TEXT>
<P>
The Metropolitan Sports Facilities Commission voted unanimously to end beer 
sales early during athletic events at the Metrodome in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
Under the change, beer sales during baseball games would end after the third 
out in the top of the eighth inning and after the third quarter of basketball 
and football games. 
</P>
