<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Neiman Marcus Group Inc.: The Chestnut Hill, Mass., retailing concern reported 
fiscal 1989 profit of $25.3 million. In 1988, the company posted a profit of 
$4.8 million using a now-discontinued accounting method; its 1988 profit would 
have been $15.5 million using its new method. Revenue increased 20% in 1989 to 
$1.5 billion. The firm said earnings for the year were reduced by the inclusion 
of results from Horchow Mail Order Inc., which had a "disappointing" 
performance following its acquisition. Each of the company's other divisions, 
including Bergdorf Goodman and Contempo Casuals, had "significantly improved 
results." 
</P>
