<P>
NISSAN TO CUT EXPORTS, PRODUCE MORE OVERSEAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japan's No. 2 auto maker Nissan Motor Co. announced Wednesday a three-point 
plan to reduce exports, increase overseas production and expand imports, 
including finished vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
The announcement coincided with newspaper reports that the government will urge 
auto makers and electronics and machinery makers not to take advantage of the 
weakening value of the Japanese yen to mount an export drive for fear of 
escalating trade friction between Japan and the United States. 
</P>
