<HEADLINE>
<P>
EASY CONSERVATION WINS AT LOS ALAMITOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Easy Conservation, winless in six previous starts this year, outran six horses 
to win the $9,000 feature race on Wednesday at Los Alamitos Race Course. 
</P>
<P>
Easy Conservation, ridden by Eddie Garcia and trained by Blane Schvaneveldt, 
covered the 350 yards in 17.86 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Easy Conservation, an 8-year-old gelding, paid $16.80, $5 and $3. Ahead Of The 
Game, which finished second, paid $3 and $2.40, third-place Providential paid 
$3.40. 
</P>
</TEXT>
