FOR THE RECORD; 
</P>
<P>
DEUKMEJIAN SIGNED JUDGES BILL IN JULY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times incorrectly reported Wednesday that legislation increasing the 
insurance and retirement benefits for San Diego County judges was signed by 
Gov. George Deukmejian last week. In fact, the bill, sponsored by Sen. Larry 
Stirling (R-San Diego), was signed into law July 13 and became effective 
immediately. Deukmejian on Tuesday announced that he had appointed Stirling as 
a San Diego Municipal Court judge, a move that will become effective with 
Stirling's resignation from the state Senate. #YES# 
</P>
</TEXT>
