<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
MOTORCYCLIST DIES IN FREEWAY CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Fontana man was killed early today when his motorcycle struck an abandoned 
vehicle with its lights off in the car-pool lane of the northbound 55 Freeway 
in Orange, a California Highway Patrol officer said. 
</P>
<P>
About 12:30 a.m., Charles Edward Earl, 40, was driving a Honda motorcycle in 
the car-pool lane at 60 to 65 m.p.h. and apparently did not see the abandoned 
Audi 4000, south of Taft Avenue, CHP Officer Keith Thornhill said. 
</P>
<P>
"He struck it in the rear causing him to be ejected from the bike, landing face 
first," Thornhill said, adding that Earl died at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
Another motorist suffered minor injuries when his vehicle, traveling in the 
freeway's fast lane, struck the motorcycle, Thornhill said. Edward Eugene 
Wyant, 32, of San Bernardino was transported to Kaiser Foundation Hospital in 
Anaheim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
