<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
ROCKWELL SUES U.S. OVER CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DENVER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rockwell International Corp. today sued the government, alleging that its 
contract to run the Rocky Flats nuclear weapons plant requires the company to 
violate federal hazardous-waste laws. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuit was filed in Washington in an attempt to get a court to clarify 
Rockwell's obligations under the contract. 
</P>
<P>
Rockwell said it was forced to sue because it feared that it would be charged 
with criminal offenses for its running of the plant near Denver. The plant 
makes plutonium triggers for nuclear weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
