<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
ARIZONAN FINDS NOTHING IMPROPER IN BARDO'S PRE-DAWN EXTRADITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHOENIX 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maricopa County Atty. Richard Romley said today his investigation concluded 
there was nothing improper in the pre-dawn extradition to Los Angeles of a 
Tucson man accused of murdering actress Rebecca Schaeffer. 
</P>
<P>
Robert John Bardo's court-appointed defense attorney in Tucson had asked Atty. 
Gen. Bob Corbin to investigate the Aug. 10 extradition, but Corbin forwarded 
the case to Romley. 
</P>
<P>
Bardo was whisked from the Pima County Jail in an Aug. 10 pre-dawn transfer 
that an assistant public defender later said violated his rights. She had filed 
her initial challenge to the extradition in the wrong court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
