<P>
EXHAUSTED STREEP QUITS 'EVITA' FILM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Academy Award-winning actress Meryl Streep has withdrawn from the film version 
of "Evita," citing exhaustion, and the film has been postponed until a new star 
is found, the producers said today. 
</P>
<P>
Director Oliver Stone said Wednesday: "I still want very much to see 'Evita' 
made. I am looking toward the future and the new singers/actresses that are 
coming up." 
</P>
<P>
Filming was to have started on the musical in Seville, Spain, next February. 
The film was to be based on the hit stage musical on the life of the late 
Argentine President Juan Peron's second wife, Eva Peron. 
