<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON CAPITALS RALLY TO WIN FINAL HOCKEY GAME AGAINST SOVIETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LENINGRAD, U.S.S.R. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Geoff Courtnall scored three goals to rally the Washington Capitals to a 5-4 
victory over a Soviet army team tonight, ending the first visit by NHL teams to 
the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
Washington and the Calgary Flames won six of eight games in the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
The Capitals fell behind 3-0 in the first period and trailed 4-1 midway through 
the second period. 
</P>
<P>
But they fought back with two goals late in the second period to trail 4-3 
entering the final 20 minutes and scored twice in the final period for the 
victory, their third in four games on the Soviet tour. 
</P>
<P>
The Stanley Cup champion Flames also won three of their four games on the tour, 
suffering their only loss Wednesday night in Moscow to the Central Army team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
